8:1 Does not wisdom cry out, and understanding lift her voice? 
8:2 On the topmost heights along the way, at the crossroads, she takes her stand. 
8:3 Beside the gates leading into the city, at the entrances, she cries aloud: 
8:4 “To you, O men, I call out! My cry is to all mankind! 
8:5 O naïve ones, learn prudence! Fools, gain understanding! 
8:6 Listen, for I speak excellent things, and my lips utter right things. 
8:7 For my mouth speaks truth, and my lips detest wickedness. 
8:8 All the words of my mouth are righteous, Nothing in them is perverse or crooked. 
8:9 All of them are straightforward to the discerning, and right to those who find knowledge. 
8:10 Receive my instruction instead of silver and knowledge rather than choice gold. 
8:11 For wisdom is better than jewels, nothing you desire compares with her. 
8:12 “I, wisdom, dwell with prudence, and acquire knowledge with discretion. 
8:13  is to hate evil. I hate pride and arrogance, evil behavior and a perverse mouth. 
8:14 Counsel and sound wisdom are mine. I have understanding and power. 
8:15 By me kings reign and princes decree justice. 
8:16 By me princes govern, and all nobles who judge righteously. 
8:17 I love those who love me. Those who earnestly seek me find me. 
8:18 With me are wealth and honor, enduring riches and righteousness. 
8:19 My fruit is better than refined gold, my harvest better than choice silver. 
8:20 I walk in the way of righteousness, along paths of justice. 
8:21 I endow substance to those who love me and fill their treasuries. 
8:22  brought me forth, the first of His way, before His works of old. 
8:23 From eternity I was appointed from the beginning, before the world began. 
8:24 When there were no depths, I was brought forth, when there were no fountains abounding with water. 
8:25 Before the mountains were shaped, before the hills, I was brought forth. 
8:26 He had not yet made the land, the fields, or the first dust of the earth. 
8:27  When He set the heavens in place, I was there. When He inscribed the horizon on the face of the ocean, 
8:28 when He established the skies above, when He securely fixed the fountains of the deep, 
8:29 when He set the boundaries for the sea, so that the waters never transgress His command, when He laid out earth’s foundations— 
8:30 then I was the craftsman beside Him, I was His daily delight, always rejoicing before Him, 
