10:1 The proverbs of Solomon. A wise son gives joy to his father, but a foolish son grief to his mother. 
10:2 Ill-gotten treasures profit nothing, but righteousness delivers from death. 
10:3  will not let a righteous soul go hungry, but thwarts the cravings of the wicked. 
10:4 Lazy hands make a man poor, but diligent hands bring wealth. 
10:5 He who gathers crops in summer is a wise son, but he who sleeps during harvest is a disgraceful son.
10:6 Blessings are on the head of the righteous, but the mouth of the wicked conceals violence. 
10:7 The memory of the righteous is a blessing, but the name of the wicked will rot. 
10:8 The wise in heart accept commands, but a babbling fool comes to ruin. 
10:9 One who walks in integrity, walks securely, but one who takes crooked paths will be discovered. 
10:10 One who winks an eye maliciously causes grief, while a babbling fool comes to ruin. 
10:11 The mouth of the righteous is a fountain of life, but the mouth of the wicked conceals violence. 
10:12 Hatred stirs up strife but love covers up all transgressions. 
10:13 Wisdom is found on the lips of the discerning, but a rod is for the back of one lacking sense. 
10:14 Wise men store up knowledge, but the mouth of a fool is near ruin. 
10:15 The wealth of a rich man is a strong city. Poverty is the ruin of the poor. 
10:16 The wages of the righteous are life. The income of the wicked is sin. 
10:17 One who heeds discipline is on the path of life, but whoever ignores correction goes astray. 
10:18 One who conceals hatred has lying lips, and whoever spreads slander is a fool. 
10:19 When words abound, transgression is unavoidable. but whoever restrains his lips is wise. 
10:20 The tongue of the righteous is choice silver. The heart of the wicked is of little value. 
10:21 The lips of the righteous feed many, but fools die for lack of understanding. 
